ng roughly half of [[New Mexico]], most of [[Arizona]], [[Nevada]], and [[Utah]], and parts of [[Wyoming]] and [[Colorado]]\n* Mexican recognition of [[Texas]] (and the [[Mexican Cession]]) as U.S. territory; End of [[Texas Revolution|conflict]] between Mexico and Texas\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Caste War of Yucat\u00e1n]]<br/>(1847&ndash;1901)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flag|Mexico|1823|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagicon image|Flag of the Republic of Yucatan.svg|size=23px}} [[Republic of Yucat\u00e1n]]<br/>{{flag|Guatemala|1843|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|United Kingdom|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|British Honduras|size=23px}}\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Maya people|Maya]]\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"| '''Victory'''\n* [[Republic of Yucat\u00e1n]] rejoins the United Mexican States in 1848\n* Mayas achieve an independent state from 1847\u20131883\n* Mexico recaptures Yucat\u00e1n\n* Conflict between the Mexicans and the Mayans continued until 1933\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Expedition of William Walker to Baja California and Sonora]]<br/>(1853)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flag|Mexico|1823|size=23px}}\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Republic of Sonora.svg|size=23px}} [[Republic of Sonora]] <br/> {{flagicon image|Flag of the Republic of Lower California.svg|size=23px}} [[Republic of Baja California]]\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"| '''Mexican Victory'''\n* Wiliam Walker trial in San Diego.\n|-\n\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Revolution of Ayutla]]<br/>(1854&ndash;1855)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Mexico|1823|size=23px}} [[Liberal Party (Mexico)|Liberals]]\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Mexico|1823|size=23px}} [[Conservative Party (Mexico)|Conservatives]]\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"| '''Liberal Victory'''\n* [[Juan \u00c1lvarez]] leads overthrow of [[Antonio L\u00f3pez de Santa Anna]]\n* Final defeat of Santa Anna and step toward the [[La Reforma|Reform]]\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Reform War]]<br/> (1857&ndash;1861)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Mexico|1823|size=23px}} [[Liberal Party (Mexico)|Liberals]]<br>{{flag|United States|1851}}\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Mexico|1823|size=23px}} [[Conservative Party (Mexico)|Conservatives]]\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"| '''Liberal Victory'''\n* [[Benito Ju\u00e1rez]] rises to power in Mexico\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Cortina Troubles]]<br/>(1859&ndash;1861)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flag|Mexico|1823|size=23px}}<br>{{flag|United States|1859}}<br>{{flag|Confederate States|1861}}\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Mexico|1823|size=23px}} Cortinista militia\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"| '''Victory'''\n* Raids ended\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Second French intervention in Mexico|Second Franco\u2013Mexican War]]<br/>(1861&ndash;1867)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flag|Mexico|1823|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|United States|1865|size=23px}}\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|France|size=23px}} [[Second French Empire|French Empire]]<br/>{{flagicon|Mexico|1864|size=23px}} [[Second Mexican Empire|Mexican Empire]]<br/>{{flag|Austrian Empire|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Belgium|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Spain|1785|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|United Kingdom|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagicon image|Flag of Egypt (1844-1867).svg|size=23px}} [[Egypt Eyalet]]<br/>{{flagicon image|Coat of arms of the January Uprising.svg|size=23px}} [[January Uprising|Polish Revolutionaries]]\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"| '''Victory'''\n* Establishment, then fall, of the [[Second Mexican Empire]]\n* French withdrawal\n* Execution of Emperor [[Maximilian I of Mexico|Maximilian I]], [[Miguel Miramon]], and [[Tomas Mejia]]\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Victorio's War]]<br/>(1879&ndash;1881)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flag|United States|1877|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|Mexico|1823|size=23px}}\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Apache]]\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"