ed by the [[United States]] through [[U.S. Ambassador to Mexico]], [[Dwight Whitney Morrow]], in order to end violence\n* Recognition of certain rights and the [[Catholic Church]] reopens in [[Mexico]] by 1929 during the presidency of [[Emilio Portes Gil]], although some anti-clerical government laws remained in place until 1992, when the [https://2001-2009.state.gov/g/drl/rls/irf/2003/24499.htm Mexican government] amended the constitution by granting all religious groups legal status, conceding them limited property rights and lifting restrictions on the number of priests in the country\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Escobar Rebellion]]<br/>(1929)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"|\n{{flagicon|Mexico|1916|size=23px}} [[ Mexican Government]]\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"|    Escobar Rebels\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"| '''Govermant Victory'''\n* Ecobar rebels defeated\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Spanish Civil War]]<br/>(1937&ndash;1939)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Spanish Republic}} [[Second Spanish Republic]]<br/>{{flag|Soviet Union|1936}}<br/>{{flagicon|Mexico|1934\u20131968|size=23px}} [[Mexico]]<br/>{{flag|France}}<br/>{{flagicon|Catalonia|size=23px}} [[Generalitat de Catalunya]]<br/>{{flagicon|Basque Country|size=23px}} [[Euzko Gudarostea]]<br/>{{flagicon image|Red star.svg}} [[Comintern]]<br/>\n{{flagicon|USA|size=23px}} [[Lincoln Battalion]]<br/>\n{{flagicon|UK|size=23px}} [[British Battalion]]<br/>\n{{-}}''[[Foreign involvement in the Spanish Civil War|Volunteers]]''\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Spain|1938}} [[Spanish Nationalists|Nationalist Spain]]<br/>{{flagcountry|Nazi Germany|size=23px}}<br/>{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy}}<br/>{{flagicon|Portugal|size=23px}} [[Portugal]]<br/>{{-}}''[[Foreign involvement in the Spanish Civil War|Volunteers]]''\n|style=\"background:#FFD0D0\"| '''Defeat'''\n* End of the Second Spanish Republic\n* Rise of the [[Francoist Spain]] Military dictatorship\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[World War II]] <br/>(1942&ndash;1945)\n[[Philippines campaign (1944\u20131945)]]\n\n[[Pacific war]]\n\n[[Battle of Luzon]]\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flag|Soviet Union|1936|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|United States|1912|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|United Kingdom|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|name=China|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|France|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Poland|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Canada|1921|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Australia|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|New Zealand|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|British Raj|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Union of South Africa|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Democratic Federal Yugoslavia|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Greece|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Denmark|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Norway|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Netherlands|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Belgium|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Luxembourg|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Czechoslovakia|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Brazil|1889|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Mexico|1934|size=23px}}<br />{{flagcountry|Ethiopian Empire|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Nepal|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Philippines|1941|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Costa Rica|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Dominican Republic|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|El Salvador|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Haiti|1941|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Honduras|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Nicaragua|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Cuba|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Guatemala|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Vietnam|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Peru|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Iraq|1921|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Bolivia|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Colombia|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Iran|1907|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Liberia|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Ecuador|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Paraguay|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Uruguay|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Venezuela|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Turkey|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Egypt|1922|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Syria|1932|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Lebanon|size=23px}}<br /> {{flag|Saudi Arabia|1938|size=23px}}<br />{{flag|Argentina|size=23px}}<br />{{fla