hes convinced to back down and peace treaty established\n* Mexican amnesty for rebels except the Edwards brothers, Martin Parmer, and Adolphus Sterne\n* A larger Mexican garrison established in Nacogdoches\n* Law restricting immigration into Texas\n* The Edwards flee to the United States (returning later for the Texas Revolution)\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Vicente Guerrero#Ouster, Capture and Execution, Dec. 1829 \u2013 Feb. 1831|Conservative Coup]]<br/>(1829&ndash;1831)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Mexico|1823|size=23px}} [[Conservative Party (Mexico)|Conservatives]]\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flagicon|Mexico|1823|size=23px}} [[Liberal Party (Mexico)|Liberals]]\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"| '''Conservative Victory'''\n* [[Anastasio Bustamante]] and [[Conservative Party (Mexico)|Conservatives]] oust liberal president [[Vicente Guerrero]] in 1829  \n* Capture and execution of Guerrero, defeat of Guerrero's forces\n|-\n\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Rebellion in Zacatecas]] <br/>(1835)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"|\n{{flagicon|Mexico|1823|size=23px}}\n[[Centralist ]]\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"|\n[[file:Flag of Zacatecas.svg|25px|border]] Zacatecan rebels\n|style=\"background:#D0FFD0\"|\n'''Centralist Victory''' \n\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Texas Revolution]]<br/>(1835&ndash;1836)\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flag|Mexico|1823|size=23px}}\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| {{flag|Republic of Texas|size=23px}}<br/>{{flag|United States|1846|size=23px}} (support)\n|style=\"background:#FFD0D0\"| '''Defeat'''\n* Texan victory, [[Treaties of Velasco]] (1836)\n* Creation of the [[Republic of Texas]] (1836)\n* [[Battle of Salado Creek (1842)|Mexican invasions of Texas]] (1842)\n* [[Texas annexation|Annexation of Texas]] by the [[United States|United States of America]] (1845); Outbreak of the [[Mexican\u2013American War]] (1846\u20131848)\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef\"| [[Pastry War|First Franco\u2013Mexican War]]<br